The exposition of the value is here for convenience but has limited capabilities. Instead, you must use [TextPattern][1] and it&#39;s [DocumentRange][2] property. This is explicitly specified [here][3]. 
From it you can use the [`GetText(-1)`][4] method to retrieve your data.

You can code it like that :

&lt;!-- language: c# --&gt;

    string GetText(AutomationElement ae)
    {
        return (ae.GetCurrentPattern(TextPattern.Pattern) as TextPattern)?.DocumentRange.GetText(-1);
    }   

  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.automation.textpattern?view=netframework-4.8
  [2]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.automation.text.textpatternrange?view=netframework-4.8
